<heading id="523681A9FF87FF81B099F9940B90F969" box="[166,945,1662,1690]" fontSize="36" level="2" pageId="2" pageNumber="511" reason="3">
<taxonomicName id="CEC14D46FF87FF81B099F9940A98F969" authority="Koretsky &amp; Holec, 2002" authorityName="Koretsky &amp; Holec" authorityYear="2002" box="[166,697,1662,1690]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Devinophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="2" pageNumber="511" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="claytoni">
<emphasis id="3BB5EAD7FF87FF81B099F99409BDF96A" bold="true" box="[166,412,1662,1689]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="511">Devinophoca claytoni</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="6D504B34FF87FF81B19DF9950A98F969" author="Koretsky, I. A. &amp; Holec, P." box="[418,697,1663,1690]" pageId="2" pageNumber="511" pagination="163 - 178" refId="ref8132" refString="Koretsky, I. A., Holec, P. 2002. A primitive seal (Mammalia: Phocidae) from the Early Middle Miocene of Central Paratethys. Smithsonian Contributions to Paleobiology, 93, 163 - 178." type="journal article" year="2002">Koretsky &amp; Holec, 2002</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="91FA2A40FF87FF81B2F7F9950B07F969" box="[712,806,1663,1690]" captionStart-0="Fig" captionStart-1="Fig" captionStart-2="Fig" captionStartId-0="1.[174,207,1765,1787]" captionStartId-1="4.[165,198,1215,1237]" captionStartId-2="5.[174,207,1640,1662]" captionTargetBox-0="[295,1120,1270,1739]" captionTargetBox-1="[205,1194,188,1176]" captionTargetBox-2="[182,1226,1098,1617]" captionTargetId-0="figure-651@1.[233,1173,1259,1764]" captionTargetId-1="figure-280@4.[198,1204,174,1183]" captionTargetId-2="figure-378@5.[174,1232,1094,1627]" captionTargetPageId-0="1" captionTargetPageId-1="4" captionTargetPageId-2="5" captionText-0="Fig. 1. Devinophoca claytoni A — incomplete skull with right M1and left P2-M1 (Z14532, holotype) and B — left mandible without ramus (SNMZ 25510; referred material) from the Museum of Natural History, Slovak National Museum, Bratislava, Slovak Republic)." captionText-1="Fig. 2. Mandibles of D. claytoni: A — labial; B — lingual; C — occlusal views. D. emryi: D — labial; E — lingual, F — occlusal views. Abbreviations: ap — angular process; con. p — condyloid process; cor. p — coronoid process; men. f — mental foramina; ms — mandibular symphysis." captionText-2="Fig. 3. Mandibles representing different subfamilies of Phocidae (true seals). A — left mandible in lingual view (SNMZ 25510, referred material) of Devinophoca claytoni (subfamily Devinophocinae). B — left mandible in lingual view of Pliophoca etrusca (subfamily Monachinae; National Museum of National History, Washington D.C., NMNH 171221). C — left mandible in labial view of Leptophoca lenis (subfamily Phocinae; Calvert Marine Museum, Maryland, CMM-V2021). D — left mandible in labial view of Cystophora cristasta (subfamily Cystophorinae, National Museum of National History, Washington D.C., NMNH 188956, female). Abbreviations: ap — angular process; con. p — condyloid process; cor. p — coronoid process; mass. fossa — masseteric fossa; men. f — mental foramina; ms — mandibular symphysis." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6455023" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6455025" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6455029" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6455023/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6455025/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/6455029/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="511">figs 1–3</figureCitation>
; tables 1–2)
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="097E36C5FF87FF81B0E4F9280C7EF92B" blockId="2.[219,1119,1730,1752]" box="[219,1119,1730,1752]" pageId="2" pageNumber="511">R e f e r r e d m a t e r i a l: SNMZ 25510, Incomplete left mandible missing ramus and most teeth.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="41DB654EFF87FF80B0E4F9150CAEFE59" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="512" pageId="2" pageNumber="511" type="description">
<paragraph id="097E36C5FF87FF81B0E4F9150CE9F8E9" blockId="2.[166,1224,1791,1850]" box="[219,1224,1791,1818]" pageId="2" pageNumber="511">
Range: Badenian, early middle Miocene (16.3–12.8 Ma; 
<bibRefCitation id="6D504B34FF87FF81B392F9150C9DF8E9" author="Wagreich, M. &amp; Hohenegger, J. &amp; Coric, S." box="[941,1212,1791,1818]" pageId="2" pageNumber="511" pagination="2013" refId="ref9092" refString="Wagreich, M., Hohenegger, J., Coric, S. 2014. Base and New Definition of the Lower Badenian and the Age of the Badenian Stratotype (Middle Miocene, Central Paratethys). In: Rocha, R., Pais, J., Kullberg, J., Finney, S., eds. STRATI 2013. Springer Geology. Springer, Cham." type="book chapter" year="2014">Wagreich et al., 2014</bibRefCitation>
);
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="097E36C5FF87FF81B099F8F50B05F8C9" blockId="2.[166,1224,1791,1850]" box="[166,804,1823,1850]" pageId="2" pageNumber="511">
Central Paratethys, Vienna Basin of Western 
<collectingCountry id="71D67655FF87FF81B284F8F50B01F8C9" box="[699,800,1823,1850]" name="Slovakia" pageId="2" pageNumber="511">Slovakia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="097E36C5FF86FF80B0DCFF450CAEFE59" blockId="3.[174,1233,175,426]" pageId="3" pageNumber="512">
A m e n d e d d i a g n o s i s: Body of mandible low in height (
<quantity id="CE399B20FF86FF80B345FF450BEFFF39" box="[890,974,175,202]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="3" pageNumber="512" unit="mm" value="12.0">12 mm</quantity>
) and retromandibular (length ~ 
<quantity id="CE399B20FF86FF80B127FF25094DFF19" box="[280,364,207,234]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" pageId="3" pageNumber="512" unit="mm" value="19.0">19 mm</quantity>
) region flat (similar to 
<taxonomicName id="CEC14D46FF86FF80B24BFF3A0AF9FF1A" baseAuthorityName="Rahmat and Koretsky" baseAuthorityYear="2016" box="[628,728,208,233]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Devinophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="512" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="emryi">
<emphasis id="3BB5EAD7FF86FF80B24BFF3A0AF9FF1A" box="[628,728,208,233]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="512">D. emryi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), with long, wide and round alveoli; mental process not present as opposed to 
<taxonomicName id="CEC14D46FF86FF80B208FF1A0ABAFEFA" baseAuthorityName="Rahmat and Koretsky" baseAuthorityYear="2016" box="[567,667,240,265]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Devinophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="512" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="emryi">
<emphasis id="3BB5EAD7FF86FF80B208FF1A0ABAFEFA" box="[567,667,240,265]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="512">D. emryi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but located between p1 and p2; symphyseal part pronounced, symphysis reaches anterior alveolus of p2 (similar to 
<taxonomicName id="CEC14D46FF86FF80B385FEFA0C01FEDA" baseAuthorityName="Rahmat and Koretsky" baseAuthorityYear="2016" box="[954,1056,272,297]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Devinophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="512" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="emryi">
<emphasis id="3BB5EAD7FF86FF80B385FEFA0C01FEDA" box="[954,1056,272,297]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="512">D. emryi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); p3–m1 tooth row oriented parallel to mandibular axis (similar to 
<taxonomicName id="CEC14D46FF86FF80B32DFEDA0B56FEBA" baseAuthorityName="Rahmat and Koretsky" baseAuthorityYear="2016" box="[786,887,304,329]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Devinophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="512" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="emryi">
<emphasis id="3BB5EAD7FF86FF80B32DFEDA0B56FEBA" box="[786,887,304,329]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="512">D. emryi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); p4 alveoli wider and longer than those of m1 (similar to 
<taxonomicName id="CEC14D46FF86FF80B1C9FEBA0A7BFE9A" baseAuthorityName="Rahmat and Koretsky" baseAuthorityYear="2016" box="[502,602,336,361]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Devinophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="512" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="emryi">
<emphasis id="3BB5EAD7FF86FF80B1C9FEBA0A7BFE9A" box="[502,602,336,361]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="512">D. emryi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); m1 single rooted (as opposed to 
<taxonomicName id="CEC14D46FF86FF80B3D8FEBA0C6AFE9A" baseAuthorityName="Rahmat and Koretsky" baseAuthorityYear="2016" box="[999,1099,336,361]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Devinophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="512" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="emryi">
<emphasis id="3BB5EAD7FF86FF80B3D8FEBA0C6AFE9A" box="[999,1099,336,361]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="512">D. emryi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with fused double-rooted m1); p2 and canine oriented obliquely to mandibular axis (as opposed to 
<taxonomicName id="CEC14D46FF86FF80B091FE7A0932FE5A" baseAuthorityName="Rahmat and Koretsky" baseAuthorityYear="2016" box="[174,275,400,425]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Devinophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="512" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="emryi">
<emphasis id="3BB5EAD7FF86FF80B091FE7A0932FE5A" box="[174,275,400,425]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="512">D. emryi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); one lower incisor (as in 
<taxonomicName id="CEC14D46FF86FF80B27CFE7A0A88FE5A" baseAuthorityName="Rahmat and Koretsky" baseAuthorityYear="2016" box="[579,681,400,425]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Devinophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="512" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="emryi">
<emphasis id="3BB5EAD7FF86FF80B27CFE7A0A88FE5A" box="[579,681,400,425]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="512">D. emryi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); diastemata absent (similar to 
<taxonomicName id="CEC14D46FF86FF80B426FE7A0C5EFE5A" baseAuthorityName="Rahmat and Koretsky" baseAuthorityYear="2016" box="[1049,1151,400,425]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Devinophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="512" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="emryi">
<emphasis id="3BB5EAD7FF86FF80B426FE7A0C5EFE5A" box="[1049,1151,400,425]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="512">D. emryi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
